9th-congress/house-bill/3176", "committeeReports": [{"url": "https://api.congress.gov/v3/committee-report/119/HRPT/291?format=json", "citation": "H. Rept. 119-291"}], "originChamberCode": "H", "updateDateIncludingText": "2026-03-24T12:48:03Z", "constitutionalAuthorityStatementText": "<pre>\\n[Congressional Record Volume 171, Number 74 (Monday, May 5, 2025)]\\n[House]\\nFrom the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href=\\"https://www.gpo.gov\\">www.gpo.gov</a>]\\nBy Mr. BEGICH:\\nH.R. 3176.\\nCongress has the power to enact this legislation pursuant\\nto the following:\\nCongress has the authority to enact this legislation\\npursuant to Article I, Section 8, Clause 3 of the United\\nStates Constitution, which grants Congress the power to\\nregulate commerce with foreign nations, among the several\\nstates, and with the Indian tribes. The National Volcano\\nEarly Warning and Monitoring System supports the monitoring\\nand early warning of volcanic activity, which directly\\nimpacts interstate and international commerce, including\\naviation, energy infrastructure, and public safety across\\nmultiple states, particularly in regions like Alaska with\\nsignificant volcanic activity. Additionally, Congress has the\\nauthority under Article I, Section 8, Clause 18, which\\nempowers Congress to make all laws necessary and proper for\\ncarrying out its enumerated powers, including ensuring the\\nsafety and economic stability of the nation through disaster\\npreparedness and response programs like the National Volcano\\nEarly Warning and Monitoring System.\\n[Page H1854]\\n</pre>"}	2026-06-03 14:20:42.087008	2026-06-03 14:20:42.087008
