1cd21b94-6efb-49ae-a703-8b92beae5721	congress.gov	119-HR-6251	https://www.congress.gov/bill/119th-congress/house-bill/6251	119	HR	6251	To amend the Marine Mammal Protection Act of 1972 to allow importation of polar bear trophies taken in sport hunts in Canada before the date the polar bear was determined to be a threatened species under the Endangered Species Act of 1973.	2025-11-21	House	Animals	2026-04-16	Subcommittee Hearings Held	2026-06-02 19:42:43	2026-06-02 19:42:43	373ecfef69e10805fc1360890c46e26c3beeef5c1c33d0ea54b130ada0d8f0fb	{"type": "HR", "title": "To amend the Marine Mammal Protection Act of 1972 to allow importation of polar bear trophies taken in sport hunts in Canada before the date the polar bear was determined to be a threatened species under the Endangered Species Act of 1973.", "number": "6251", "titles": {"url": "https://api.congress.gov/v3/bill/119/hr/6251/titles?format=json", "count": 2}, "actions": {"url": "https://api.congress.gov/v3/bill/119/hr/6251/actions?format=json", "count": 5}, "congress": 119, "sponsors": [{"url": "https://api.congress.gov/v3/member/B001323?format=json", "party": "R", "state": "AK", "fullName": "Rep. Begich, Nicholas J. [R-AK-At Large]", "lastName": "Begich", "firstName": "Nicholas", "bioguideId": "B001323", "middleName": "J.", "isByRequest": "N"}], "subjects": {"url": "https://api.congress.gov/v3/bill/119/hr/6251/subjects?format=json", "count": 8}, "committees": {"url": "https://api.congress.gov/v3/bill/119/hr/6251/committees?format=json", "count": 1}, "cosponsors": {"url": "https://api.congress.gov/v3/bill/119/hr/6251/cosponsors?format=json", "count": 1, "countIncludingWithdrawnCosponsors": 1}, "policyArea": {"name": "Animals"}, "updateDate": "2026-06-02T19:42:43Z", "latestAction": {"text": "Subcommittee Hearings Held", "actionDate": "2026-04-16"}, "textVersions": {"url": "https://api.congress.gov/v3/bill/119/hr/6251/text?format=json", "count": 1}, "originChamber": "House", "introducedDate": "2025-11-21", "legislationUrl": "https://www.congress.gov/bill/119th-congress/house-bill/6251", "originChamberCode": "H", "updateDateIncludingText": "2026-06-02T19:42:43Z", "constitutionalAuthorityStatementText": "<pre>\\n[Congressional Record Volume 171, Number 197 (Friday, November 21, 2025)]\\n[House]\\nFrom the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href=\\"https://www.gpo.gov\\">www.gpo.gov</a>]\\nBy Mr. BEGICH:\\nH.R. 6251.\\nCongress has the power to enact this legislation pursuant\\nto the following:\\nCongress has the power to enact this legislation pursuant\\nto the following provisions of the Constitution of the United\\nStates:\\nArticle I, Section 8, Clause 3 (the Commerce Clause), which\\ngrants Congress the authority to regulate commerce with\\nforeign nations. The bill amends the Marine Mammal Protection\\nAct to govern the importation of certain polar bear parts\\nfrom Canada, an activity squarely within foreign commerce.\\nArticle I, Section 8, Clause 18 (the Necessary and Proper\\nClause), which authorizes Congress to make all laws necessary\\nand proper for carrying into execution the foregoing powers,\\nincluding regulation of wildlife importation and permitting\\nunder federal law.\\n[Page H4896]\\n</pre>"}	2026-06-03 15:15:58.894957	2026-06-03 15:15:58.894957
